# Implementation Steps

## 1. Configured Route Tables

Updated the route table associated with the public subnet to direct outbound internet traffic (0.0.0.0/0) through the Internet Gateway.

---

## 2. Configured Security Groups

Created Security Group rules allowing inbound HTTP traffic while relying on the default outbound rule to permit return traffic.

This demonstrated the stateful behavior of Security Groups.

---

## 3. Configured Network ACLs

Reviewed the default Network ACL and explored how custom ACLs can explicitly allow or deny traffic at the subnet level.

This demonstrated the stateless nature of Network ACLs.

---

## 4. Compared Security Layers

Examined how Route Tables, Security Groups, and Network ACLs work together to determine whether traffic ultimately reaches an AWS resource.

